<div id="review_3469765073" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3469765073" />
    <a title="Charlie Hasler" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/74466071-charlie-hasler"><img alt="Charlie Hasler" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1539117251p2/74466071.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3469765073?book_show_action=true">Nov 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlie Hasler" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlie Hasler" href="/user/show/74466071-charlie-hasler">Charlie Hasler</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781784871512" href="/book/show/38323506-the-gulag-archipelago">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3469765073" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6124390795116501691">As I don&apos;t have a Kindle I took pictures on my phone of parts that stopped me dead. After further reading and picture taking, I now have an Archipelago folder on my phone. I did this because the words and points made so utterly shattered and moved me that I felt it so important I revisit these pages in the future. <br/><br/>The writing style reminded me of reading Henri Charrieres Papillon. Fast, to the point, and powerful.<br/><br/>Probably one of the most important books I will ever read.</span>
  <span id="freeText6124390795116501691" style="display:none">As I don't have a Kindle I took pictures on my phone of parts that stopped me dead. After further reading and picture taking, I now have an Archipelago folder on my phone. I did this because the words and points made so utterly shattered and moved me that I felt it so important I revisit these pages in the future. <br /><br />The writing style reminded me of reading Henri Charrieres Papillon. Fast, to the point, and powerful.<br /><br />Probably one of the most important books I will ever read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6124390795116501691" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
